<paragraph id="96782E5E9577FFF130911363CFB0C58F" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
Remarks. Examined specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="EED06ECE9577FFF132271363CEF9C5DF" box="[597,695,362,384]" name="Colombia" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Colombia</collectingCountry>
: Milán have extremely long stalked eyes on male, as long as in most examined specimens from Central America (
<figureCitation id="0EFC32DB9577FFF132B1138DCF5EC5C5" box="[707,784,388,410]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1747,1769]" captionTargetBox="[197,1179,934,1719]" captionTargetId="figure-249@2.[196,1179,934,1719]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–11. Plagiocephalus latifrons (1–8 — Ơ: 1–6 —from Panama, 7 — from Colombia: Milán, 8 — from Colombia: Florencia, 9–11 — ♀ from Peru): 1, 5, 7–9, — habitus (1, 7, 8 — dorsal, 5 — left, 9 — anterior view); 2 — head, frontal view, 3 — head and thorax, dorsal view; 4, 10 — face, anterior view; 6 — abdomen; 11 — abdomen and wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454114/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">figs 1–7</figureCitation>
), whereas the specimens collected in Florencia (
<figureCitation id="0EFC32DB9577FFF130C61396CCA8C5EA" box="[180,230,415,437]" captionStart="Figs 1–11" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1747,1769]" captionTargetBox="[197,1179,934,1719]" captionTargetId="figure-249@2.[196,1179,934,1719]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–11. Plagiocephalus latifrons (1–8 — Ơ: 1–6 —from Panama, 7 — from Colombia: Milán, 8 — from Colombia: Florencia, 9–11 — ♀ from Peru): 1, 5, 7–9, — habitus (1, 7, 8 — dorsal, 5 — left, 9 — anterior view); 2 — head, frontal view, 3 — head and thorax, dorsal view; 4, 10 — face, anterior view; 6 — abdomen; 11 — abdomen and wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454114/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">fig. 8</figureCitation>
) have conspicuously shorter eyestalks, as described for 
<taxonomicName id="51C755DD9577FFF1337013A9C865C5EA" authority="Kameneva, 2004" authorityName="Kameneva" authorityYear="2004" box="[770,1067,415,437]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" genus="Plagiocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="A4B3F24C9577FFF1337013A9CFCDC5EB" box="[770,899,415,437]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">P. intermedia</emphasis>
Kameneva, 2004
</taxonomicName>
; these specimens have wing pattern typical for 
<taxonomicName id="51C755DD9577FFF131B513B3CE61C590" authorityName=": Steyskal" authorityYear="1968" box="[455,559,442,463]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" genus="Plagiocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifrons">
<emphasis id="A4B3F24C9577FFF131B513B3CE61C590" box="[455,559,442,463]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">P. latifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and we consider this to be individual variation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
